1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:35,220
=The Tale of Rose=

2
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:39,140
=Episode 18=

3
00:01:39,790 --> 00:01:40,630
Su,

4
00:01:40,980 --> 00:01:42,430
it's been a long time
since I heard from you.

5
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:44,310
I miss you a lot.

6
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:47,310
Last time, I didn't handle things well

7
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:48,980
and said things I shouldn't have.

8
00:01:50,740 --> 00:01:52,150
When faced with pain,

9
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:53,870
some people cry their hearts out,

10
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:56,820
and others grit their teeth
and say nothing.

11
00:01:57,950 --> 00:01:59,670
I shouldn't have encouraged you
to scream,

12
00:02:00,340 --> 00:02:02,230
but should have held your hand tightly.

13
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:04,550
I'm sorry.

14
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:06,980
♪Through every battle♪

15
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:07,820
I'm leaving.

16
00:02:08,820 --> 00:02:10,340
♪In our hearts♪

17
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:12,380
♪The fire will ignite♪

18
00:02:12,940 --> 00:02:14,150
Remember to buy some food on the way.

19
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:15,580
Don't worry.

20
00:02:15,590 --> 00:02:16,430
Bye.

21
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,270
Hi, Morning.

22
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:21,550
- Morning.
- Morning.

23
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:28,100
♪But we will stand again♪

24
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,030
I'm looking for a job.

25
00:02:31,430 --> 00:02:32,600
But what's more important than a job

26
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,940
is finding the direction for the future.

27
00:02:37,940 --> 00:02:40,620
♪With hope and love♪

28
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:46,220
♪We will break the chains♪

29
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:50,620
♪Forever we will shine♪

30
00:02:50,780 --> 00:02:54,620
Being a mother is not easy.

31
00:02:56,270 --> 00:02:59,740
I've worked hard, changing diapers
and cleaning up after you.

32
00:02:59,740 --> 00:03:01,710
I raised you.

33
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:05,900
Now you're trying to take my house.

34
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:10,430
You're trying to kill us all.

35
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:20,310
Why is my life so miserable?

36
00:03:34,660 --> 00:03:36,460
You want to take my house?

37
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:38,180
Don't think about it.

38
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:40,110
Let me tell you.

39
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:43,870
I'll never transfer this house
to you, even if I die.

40
00:03:44,340 --> 00:03:45,780
Don't even think about it.

41
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:48,060
You're making me so angry.

42
00:03:52,110 --> 00:03:53,030
I've raised you for so long.

43
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:54,180
Now that we are in trouble,

44
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:56,110
what's wrong
with helping us with some money?

45
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,550
You still want to take this house?

46
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:05,830
I just can't live like this.

47
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,510
You shouldn't have given them the money.

48
00:04:21,590 --> 00:04:23,460
After giving the money to them,

49
00:04:24,780 --> 00:04:25,950
he ran away again.

50
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:27,460
He hasn't been home for days.

51
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:30,540
Mom's at home crying and making a scene,

52
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:31,860
and she's always venting her anger on me.

53
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,180
Gengsheng,

54
00:04:42,340 --> 00:04:44,270
you don't need to buy me these things.

55
00:04:44,860 --> 00:04:45,780
I'm working now

56
00:04:46,030 --> 00:04:47,300
and making some money myself.

57
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:50,660
Hasn't your money

58
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:53,460
been taken away by them?

59
00:04:54,420 --> 00:04:55,390
How much money do you have left?

60
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,140
Gengsheng,

61
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:00,540
I know you hate me.

62
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:02,140
Why?

63
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,420
Because of that thing.

64
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,390
I really don't remember.

65
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:14,460
I'm sorry.

66
00:05:19,630 --> 00:05:20,980
You're an adult now.

67
00:05:21,590 --> 00:05:22,830
What can he do to you?

68
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,200
Why are you still so afraid of him?

69
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:51,570
Do I need to change my shoes?

70
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,700
No.

71
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:58,710
This is your home? It's small.

72
00:06:00,270 --> 00:06:01,630
It's just an attic.

73
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:26,190
During this time,
I've been thinking a lot.

74
00:06:30,460 --> 00:06:31,590
Those negative emotions

75
00:06:31,590 --> 00:06:33,100
from my problems

76
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:35,420
shouldn't be vented on you.

77
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:38,030
I haven't even met him,

78
00:06:39,070 --> 00:06:40,220
and it wasn't fair for me

79
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,100
to judge your relationship so harshly.

80
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:43,350
It's my fault.

81
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:45,270
I'm sorry.

82
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:48,460
Are you in Shanghai just to apologize?

83
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:50,630
Stop flattering yourself.

84
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:52,060
Just passing by.

85
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:55,510
- You are.
- I'm passing by.

86
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:40,500
Xiaohe?

87
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:45,030
It's really you.

88
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:47,340
I thought it was you from over there.

89
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,350
Long time no see.

90
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:50,980
Yeah, what a coincidence.

91
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,510
Do you still remember this place?

92
00:07:53,460 --> 00:07:54,300
Yeah.

93
00:07:54,340 --> 00:07:55,300
The first time I went fishing

94
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,510
was with you.

95
00:07:57,150 --> 00:07:58,420
Then I'm your mentor.

96
00:07:58,830 --> 00:08:00,070
It's my honor.

97
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:02,460
Will I bother you if I stay here?

98
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:03,870
Of course not.

99
00:08:04,030 --> 00:08:05,750
Fishing is about enjoying the waiting.

100
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,660
Whether you catch anything
depends on fate.

101
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:09,950
That's right.

102
00:08:10,390 --> 00:08:11,230
Let's keep fishing.

103
00:08:11,590 --> 00:08:12,430
Okay.

104
00:08:23,630 --> 00:08:24,750
You're still young.

105
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,190
How did you manage to develop this habit?

106
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:29,340
Isn't there an age limit for fishing?

107
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,270
You're not much older than me.

108
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:32,940
Don't you like fishing?

109
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:34,420
Fishing is good for health.

110
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:35,990
It exercises your mind and body

111
00:08:36,230 --> 00:08:37,420
without being too intense.

112
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:39,500
Especially suitable for us
middle-aged people

113
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:41,150
who spend a lot of time in the office,

114
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:42,390
can't stop thinking,

115
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,300
and can't keep up with physical activity.

116
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:46,390
You're not that old.

117
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:49,540
I look fine, right?

118
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:51,990
But not as good as when I was younger.

119
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:55,390
Ten years ago, I could stay up all night
dancing and drinking,

120
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:57,180
and the next day
I could still get up for work.

121
00:08:57,660 --> 00:08:58,580
Can't do that now.

122
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,150
I can't even drink Chinese white wine.

123
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:01,230
A sip makes me dizzy.

124
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:02,940
I don't know if the problem

125
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:03,900
is with the liquor or me.

126
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:05,940
They say good liquor
doesn't get you drunk,

127
00:09:05,940 --> 00:09:07,390
but it just has fewer other alcohols.

128
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:09,270
It's high in methanol content,

129
00:09:09,630 --> 00:09:10,920
which is hard for the body to metabolize.

130
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:11,830
So,

131
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:13,150
can I understand it this way?

132
00:09:13,540 --> 00:09:15,540
If I drink 100% pure alcohol,
I won't get drunk.

133
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:16,500
No, that's not possible.

134
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,150
Alcohol can cause acidosis,

135
00:09:18,580 --> 00:09:19,700
affecting the body's potassium,

136
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:20,870
sodium, chloride, and other ions,

137
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:22,150
and causing nerve damage.

138
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:28,350
You're joking with me again.

139
00:09:29,180 --> 00:09:30,470
You're still the same serious

140
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:33,540
and meticulous
when it comes to your profession.

141
00:09:34,940 --> 00:09:37,700
So someone like me
with such low emotional intelligence

142
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:40,540
should just stay in school.

143
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:43,710
You graduated, right?

144
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:44,830
What do you do?

145
00:09:45,540 --> 00:09:47,700
I don't know anything except studying.

146
00:09:48,180 --> 00:09:50,630
I'm applying for a position
in a chemical lab

147
00:09:50,820 --> 00:09:52,700
at the Chinese Academy of Sciences.

148
00:09:52,940 --> 00:09:54,180
I'm still waiting for news.

149
00:09:54,390 --> 00:09:55,750
I was anxious these past two days,

150
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:56,780
so I came out to fish.

151
00:09:56,990 --> 00:09:58,820
The Chinese Academy of Sciences.

152
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:01,060
I'm in awe.

153
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:04,060
The result hasn't come out yet.

154
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:05,470
In my eyes,

155
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:08,350
researchers are potential
Nobel Prize winners.

156
00:10:10,940 --> 00:10:11,820
How's it going?

157
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:13,780
Are you still single?

158
00:10:15,630 --> 00:10:16,780
Right now,

159
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:19,270
I'm just thinking about the job,

160
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:21,110
nothing else.

161
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,230
How about you?

162
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:24,260
Me?

163
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:26,110
I just gained weight.

164
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,720
If only the stock market
were like my weight,

165
00:10:27,730 --> 00:10:28,870
so it would only go up, never down.

166
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:29,940
Everyone would be happy about it.

167
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:44,190
I'll help you.

168
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:47,270
How can I let a guest do it?

169
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:48,630
You two go ahead and chat.

170
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:50,390
We can make it quicker.

171
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:51,830
Okay.

172
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:53,440
Are these dishes to be washed?

173
00:10:53,470 --> 00:10:54,310
Yes.

174
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:09,420
Did she ask you to evaluate me?

175
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:11,580
She trusts those she chooses.

176
00:11:11,780 --> 00:11:12,940
She doesn't care

177
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:14,150
whose opinion it is

178
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,230
unless you care.

179
00:11:17,660 --> 00:11:20,660
Of course, I want everyone's approval.

180
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:23,990
I always feel

181
00:11:25,470 --> 00:11:26,540
I'm not good enough for her.

182
00:12:04,820 --> 00:12:06,030
I've figured it out.

183
00:12:06,230 --> 00:12:07,780
You're like Jiang Taigong fishing.

184
00:12:07,780 --> 00:12:09,180
Whether you catch the fish
doesn't matter.

185
00:12:09,780 --> 00:12:11,180
You're here to enjoy the scenery,

186
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:12,230
to relax.

187
00:12:13,390 --> 00:12:15,470
Fishing is really relaxing.

188
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:16,630
I didn't realize it before,

189
00:12:17,060 --> 00:12:18,270
but later I found

190
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:20,180
this activity really suits me.

191
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:22,350
Let's do it together when we have time.

192
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:24,580
Okay. My car's here.

193
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:27,700
Last time your sister came along.

194
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:28,540
How's she doing now?

195
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:30,420
She's graduated from graduate school

196
00:12:30,540 --> 00:12:31,380
and stayed in Shanghai.

197
00:12:31,420 --> 00:12:33,230
She'll probably settle down
and start a family there.

198
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:34,830
That's great.

199
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:37,940
I'm very happy to see you today.

200
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:39,580
I'm really happy too.

201
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,510
Happier than catching a rainbow trout.

202
00:12:42,390 --> 00:12:43,300
Well, I'll be going now.

203
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:49,020
Keep in touch.

204
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:49,900
Okay.

205
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:53,660
I'm leaving.

206
00:12:54,230 --> 00:12:55,070
Bye-bye.

207
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:12,500
Tastes good.

208
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:14,700
Are the dishes not enough?

209
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:15,870
I'll cook more.

210
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,030
- No, no, it's enough.
- It's enough, enough.

211
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:18,900
The food you made is so delicious.

212
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:19,820
We couldn't waste it.

213
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:21,760
Since you're done,

214
00:13:21,780 --> 00:13:23,470
why don't you two go upstairs and chat?

215
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:24,540
I'll tidy up a bit.

216
00:13:24,670 --> 00:13:25,550
Let me help you.

217
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:26,900
No, nobody needs to lift a finger.

218
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:27,900
I'll do it myself.

219
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:29,590
Go ahead.

220
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:31,510
Okay. Let's go upstairs then.

221
00:13:32,030 --> 00:13:32,870
Thank you.

222
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:34,070
No problem.

223
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:54,820
Can you objectively
evaluate him this time?

224
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:10,660
I want

225
00:14:12,180 --> 00:14:13,660
to objectively evaluate you.

226
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:18,110
You don't need to do anything now.

227
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:20,990
- Really?
- Of course.

228
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:36,700
Now I see why you thought we were alike.

229
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:39,030
He's just like me.

230
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:40,420
Insecure,

231
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:42,110
so extremely sensitive.

232
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:45,900
We always try to perfect ourselves

233
00:14:46,110 --> 00:14:47,540
before others can criticize us.

234
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,300
But his insecurity
makes him gentle, caring,

235
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:52,740
and understanding towards you.

236
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:53,620
I can't do that.

237
00:14:55,660 --> 00:14:56,500
Su,

238
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:59,150
you're actually very gentle.

239
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:00,870
Come on.

240
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:09,510
How are you doing lately?

241
00:15:17,470 --> 00:15:18,310
Pretty good.

242
00:15:32,580 --> 00:15:34,380
(Hetang Yuese)

243
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:39,660
You're online.

244
00:15:42,310 --> 00:15:44,060
(Hetang Yuese)
Are you going fishing next weekend?

245
00:15:54,060 --> 00:15:54,900
Yes.

246
00:15:58,270 --> 00:15:59,180
Let's meet at the usual spot.

247
00:16:02,540 --> 00:16:04,340
(Hetang Yuese)

248
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:11,350
Okay. Let's take a photo together.

249
00:16:11,630 --> 00:16:12,510
Everyone, be happy.

250
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:13,610
Ready?

251
00:16:13,660 --> 00:16:14,500
Three,

252
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:15,420
two,

253
00:16:15,470 --> 00:16:16,310
one.

254
00:16:18,350 --> 00:16:20,900
Congratulations on graduating!

255
00:16:23,630 --> 00:16:24,940
I want us to hug together.

256
00:16:29,510 --> 00:16:31,610
I recommended you to Mr. He,
chief editor at the publishing house.

257
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:33,110
He heard about your grades

258
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:34,780
and wanted you to report immediately.

259
00:16:35,150 --> 00:16:36,060
Thank you.

260
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:38,660
They don't have any
budgeted posts available this year.

261
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:40,300
Can you accept an unbudgeted one?

262
00:16:40,470 --> 00:16:41,310
No problem.

263
00:16:41,630 --> 00:16:43,900
This job is
a learning opportunity anyway.

264
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:45,470
I plan to work and study

265
00:16:45,470 --> 00:16:47,990
to be a certified
counseling psychologist.

266
00:16:48,270 --> 00:16:49,110
I knew it.

267
00:16:49,350 --> 00:16:50,990
You were never one for comfort.

268
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:54,140
Let's go.

269
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,390
You didn't pay attention to P.E. classes
when you were a kid, right?

270
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,270
You can't just use your arm.

271
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:04,190
You have to use your waist.

272
00:17:04,910 --> 00:17:06,510
Like this or like this.

273
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:08,270
This is my first time with lure fishing.

274
00:17:09,060 --> 00:17:09,900
You reel it in first.

275
00:17:10,510 --> 00:17:11,350
Ready?

276
00:17:13,620 --> 00:17:14,460
Hold it firmly.

277
00:17:14,620 --> 00:17:15,460
You see?

278
00:17:16,340 --> 00:17:19,060
Ready? One, two, three.

279
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:24,710
- Reel it in.
- It's quite far.

280
00:17:25,230 --> 00:17:26,470
Yes, like this.

281
00:17:27,230 --> 00:17:28,430
You see? Your hand can...

282
00:17:28,620 --> 00:17:29,580
No, don't hold it so high.

283
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:30,470
Lower it a bit.

284
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:32,430
Then reel in the line.

